<node><name>Prepare Activity</name>
<id>3</id>
<lefticon>undefined</lefticon>
<righticon>curation</righticon>
<column>OOCI</column>
<textHTML>&lt;p&gt;Prepare a list of terms that students will need to categorize during the activity. The terms should relate clearly to one of the categories they need to understand.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Example:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;In a Rationalist and Empiricist activity, the terms used in this activity include anything from names of philosophers, terminology used in the study of epistemology, to phrases that express ideas of either the rationalists or empiricists. It can even include graphic representations of concepts. For a more detailed list of the terms used in this activity, please see the &lt;a href="https://www.saltise.ca/resources/materials/categorizing-forâ€¦-example-answers/" target="_blank"&gt;Rationalist and Empiricist Answers document&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Note:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;This is a review activity, so the terms should be things they have already seen before. However, you can also include short phrases that express certain concepts that relate to the different categories.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You can also include terms that might not fit exactly into either category, but might branch between the two. This challenges the students to think outside the categories as well.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;If there are enough smartboards in the classroom for each group, this activity can be prepared in the smartboards app. Students can move the terms around on the smartboard&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Low Tech Version&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Use color paper and sticky tack&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Prepare a document with all of the terms, including the terms for the general categories&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Print each term large enough to be put out as a distinct piece of paper. Then cut each term or word out so that you have a packet of terms&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create enough of these packets for each group. It helps if each packet of terms is printed on a different color paper. This makes it easier to keep the packets together for future use.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;</textHTML>
